label.value: modulation by host of viral transcription

definition.value: Any process in which a host organism modulates the frequency, rate or extent of viral transcription.

label.value: negative regulation by host of viral transcription

definition.value: Any process in which a host organism stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of viral transcription.

label.value: positive regulation by host of viral transcription

definition.value: Any process is which a host organism activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of viral transcription, the synthesis of either RNA on a template of DNA or DNA on a template of RNA.
